    • toString

      public java.lang.String toString()
      Description copied from interface: Type
      Yields a string representing this type. The string should be consistent with equality. That is, if this.equals(anotherType), then it should be that this.toString().equals(anotherType.toString()). The string is not necessarily a legal type expression in the language, such as a Java identifier. It is suggested, but not required, that it be an easily human-readable representation that can be used both in error messages and in generated output.
